##An oral history | family of three in Wuhan: "Wandering" , "epidemic not our fault"

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Check-in counter, the staff saw the passport issued by Hubei, subconsciously to hide back, then picked up the phone, said something in English.

Dictation | Wang Feng

Tidying | Wu Xue

Dictation | Wang Feng

Tidying | Wu Xue

Wuhan Mayor Zhou Xianwang said at a news conference on January 26 that more than 5 million Wuhan people have left Wuhan, and our family of three is one of these 5 million people -- a "Wuhan Wanderer. ".

My name is Wang Feng. I am an employee of a securities company in Wuhan. A few days ago, hearing the news of Li Wenliang's death, I felt very sad. On December 31, I saw a screenshot of Dr. Li saying there was an infectious disease on my friends' circle. When I asked my classmates at Wuhan Central Hospital, I was told, "there are many people who have this disease, and the situation is really serious. ".

I work only two kilometers away from the south China Seafood Market, so I dare not take it lightly. In early January, my family put on masks with vigilance.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
With my daughter in Australia

The annual Spring Festival outing is a tradition in my family. I chose to go to Australia after consulting with my lover this year. Many people asked me if I knew that the city would be closed to escape from Wuhan. Actually, no. The discount tickets were booked six months ago, when we didn't know it was GONNA be as bad as it is today. The only concern was that my 3 year old daughter had just been hospitalized with pneumonia in December, and it had been snowing in Wuhan for two days, and it was the middle of a flu outbreak, so what if the temperature at the airport was abnormal and she couldn't fly.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
For a family of three

There is no direct flight to Melbourne from Wuhan. The ticket is booked from Pudong, Shanghai. On the night of January 18th, my family took a high speed train to Shanghai Hongqiao Railway Station, lugging two large suitcases, and then took a taxi to Pudong Airport. Not many people on the high speed train wore masks, and neither did the taxi drivers. At that time, academician Zhong Nanshan had not yet reported any symptoms of "human-to-human transmission" , and airport security checks were proceeding as usual. It went well. We were in Melbourne by noon the next day. My daughter had a great time during her five days in Melbourne.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The daughter's in the University of Technology Sydney

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
My daughter runs in the open meadows of Australia

But also in these 5 days, Wuhan has undergone earth-shaking changes. On January 20, Zhong Nanshan confirmed human to human transmission and reported infection among medical staff; on January 23, the city of Wuhan was closed. On January 24, Hubei Province launched a first-level emergency response to a public health emergency. Parents in Wuhan called to say they had gone to the supermarket to snap up dishes and were ready to stay indoors for a long time, the bustling streets of Jianghan Street and Hubu Alley in the past have also become empty.

Watching the increase in cases on the news, as a "sensitive" Wuhan people, I began to worry about a series of issues. For example, the Wuhan to Shanghai high-speed Rail, there will be infected people, although we did not dare to take off the mask; for example, the Australian hotel will not receive Wuhan people, the flight back to the country will be blocked, and so on. In fact, at that time Australia was not so strict and did not treat Hubei tourists specially.

January 25, because the fire has not been put out, originally intended to drive to Sydney, we chose to buy tickets to go. On January 29, the day before he was due to return home, six people in Australia had been diagnosed with new crown pneumonia. That day, the Australian Prime Minister, Morrison, announced the evacuation of overseas Chinese from Wuhan, in Hubei Province. The next day, all non stop flights from Sydney to Wuhan were cancelled. The next journey home, let me feel the Hubei Tourists "special treatment. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wife and daughter at the airport

After the ticket was cancelled, I had my heart set on going to Hainan, where the weather was nice and the children were comfortable. But I didn't have a direct flight to Hainan, so I booked Hong Kong first, then from Hong Kong to Hainan. But then Hong Kong has restricted entry Hubei people, plus our luggage, we need to re-entry, so plan a rejected.

Plan B is to fly straight to Kunming, where there is a suitable flight. Plan C is to stay in Australia for a while, wait for the situation to improve, then return home. Considering the children are still small, once there is a headache fever in Australia, not only language, all aspects may not as convenient as domestic. Of course, we were worried that if the hotel wouldn't let us stay there, we would risk sleeping on the street. After discussion, we decided on option B -- Foshan -- to fly straight to Kunming.

On February 2, we boarded a flight to Kunming at Sydney International Airport, which was very different from our arrival a week earlier. Most of the staff at security checkpoints and ticket counters wore masks, but not many of the tourists, with only a few asian-looking Chinese, Koreans and Japanese wearing masks. Check-in counter, the staff saw the passport issued by Hubei, subconsciously to hide back, then picked up the phone, said something in English.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
China Eastern check-in counter

Soon, two airport officials came to us and said in less-than-fluent Chinese, "excuse me, can we make a separate check-in? " We cooperated, and they took our temperature with a hand-warming gun first, then we asked about the itinerary and basic information, and signed a health pledge, and finally, we went to another empty counter, this is completed check-in.

Since most of the people on this flight were from Yunnan, the three of US boarded the plane, sat in the last row, wearing masks the whole time, and did not move around. The China Eastern flight attendants on the plane had professional training and did not look at us in particular. In fact, my wife and I did not know Kunming's treatment of tourists in Hubei Situation, at first was a little worried.

After landing in Kunming at 5:30 am on February 3, the China Eastern flight crew first let passengers from Yunnan get off the plane, then the customs brought people from the Center for Disease Control and Prevention up to take body temperature, and then we were taken to the "symptomatic tourist observation room" to learn about our physical condition, it took a total of two hours to track the journey. Fortunately, there were no fever people on board, or it might have taken longer.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
China border exit

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Kunming Airport Symptom Observation Room

At that time, we were received by a fellow townsman from Hubei. He said, you don't have to worry. Here in Kunming, there are some hotels for "asymptomatic tourists from Hubei" , where they can stay for free, as long as 14 days. After isolation and confirmation of no symptoms, you can buy tickets to other cities in Kunming. I breathed a sigh of relief, and now I don't have to worry about wandering around anymore. The airport sent a special car to take us to the designated hotel, Geum River Star, the hotel front desk although "armed" , but very warm to receive us.

The star of Geum River was a quick hotel, and the three of us were put in a standard room. Three Meals a Day, two meat and a vegetarian plus white rice, food is very good, Kunming is rich in fruit, one day apple, bananas, oranges, Breakfast and Yogurt. If you want to eat something else, the hotel can also help in the vicinity of the designated restaurants to order takeout, just to pay for a stir-fry.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Daughter's eating at a hotel

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yogurt and fruit from the hotel

Designated hotels serve more than three meals a day, community doctors visit twice a day to monitor body temperature and police are stationed nearby in order to keep visitors healthy and avoid cross contamination at the hospital. If there are any small needs, such as medicine or other small needs, you can inform the hotel staff, and then they help to buy on behalf of.

Recently, the Dali Health Bureau intercepted "nine masks sent from Ruili to Chongqing" , it is really chilling, the more difficult the epidemic prevention, the more must follow and obey the law. However, the improper practice of a certain region, a place "total negation" is also one-sided. For example, this time to stranded in Yunnan tourists in Hubei, Hubei people around me, are particularly grateful and touched.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Hotel staff are performing routine disinfection

As far as I know, on January 26, the Yunnan Provincial Department of Culture and tourism issued a notice to at least 16 provinces and cities to identify a hotel for stranded tourists in Yunnan. On January 30th Kunming announced seven hotels as observation points. At present, more than 2300 tourists stranded in Kunming have been properly settled. On February 8, our family also ate the "heart-warming glutinous rice balls" sent by the hotel. Although we were in other places, we felt the same warmth as home.

In contrast, some of my fellow countrymen may not be so lucky. One of my colleagues who was stranded on a family visit had to go to his local street office, police Married... with Children, and get a health certificate before checking into a hotel, there are also tourists from Hubei Province who have been turned away and have had to find a bed and breakfast. I also read on Weibo that a person from Inner Mongolia was not allowed to book a hotel because he used a Wuhan mobile phone number Another mother took her child to Shandong, because when she got on the plane she spoke a Wuhan dialect, and the people traveling with her did not want to fly on the same plane with them, so they had to change their tickets.

I was talking with my friend, he said with deep feeling, now it seems that people are not quarantined patients, but quarantined Wuhan people. The outbreak took place in Wuhan. The victims were first and foremost residents of Wuhan. The outbreak in Wuhan was not our fault. In fact, we were quite aggrieved. This Spring Festival, to Kunming but 9 days, but as if after a long time, we want to go home, hope that the epidemic as soon as possible, road closure, we can go back and family reunion.

The pictures in this article are provided by the interviewees
